{"cards":[{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Electromagnetic radiation waves"},{"type":"headline","text":"Are made up of electric, magnetic fields"},{"type":"bullet","text":"Fields are perpendicular to <u>each other<\/u>"},{"type":"headline","text":"Are transverse waves so"},{"type":"bullet","text":"Fields also perpendicular to <u>wave direction<\/u>"}]},{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Speed of light"},{"type":"headline","text":"Early scientists thought it was infinite"},{"type":"headline","text":"Galileo attempted to measure its speed"}]}],"definitions":[],"secText":["  <b>Essential Question: <\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>How can we quantify the electric and magnetic fields that compose light?","  <b>Enduring Understandings:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='19' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>Electromagnetic radiation<\/a> is composed of magnetic and electric fields. The strength of each field <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='19' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='1'>changes<\/a> over time. The electric and magnetic fields have the same frequency, are in phase, and are perpendicular to each other.<br \/>2. The <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='19' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>speed of light<\/a> is equal to 3.0\u00d710<sup class=\"\">8<\/sup> m\/s.","  <b>Vocabulary:<\/b>  <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='19' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>electromagnetic radiation<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='19' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='2'>electromagnetic spectrum<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='19' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>speed of light<\/a>","  <b>STEM Skills:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='15' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='1'>electric fields<\/a>.<br \/>2. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='17' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='1'>magnetic fields<\/a>.<br \/>3. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='13' data-topic='4' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>transverse waves<\/a>."],"objNames":["wb_em_waves_concepts1","wb_light_speed1"]}